    <section class="section-paragraph section-faqs">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">SEO Director FAQs</h2>
            <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage" class="row">
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse1">
                            <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What is local and national SEO?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse1" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Local and national SEO (search engine optimisation) is the process of improving search engine visibility for local brick-and-mortar businesses. With local and national SEO, you can build your online presence and target customers in the areas that you serve.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse2">
                            <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">Why is local and national SEO important?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse2" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Local and national SEO is the bread and butter of brick-and-mortar businesses. Nearly half of Google queries are local searches, which means users are actively looking for location-based results. Google also has a specific set of ranking factors to measure whether your business is geographically relevant to a user performing a local search.</p>
                                <p>This allows local businesses to target local and national customers without competing with the likes of large corporations – not only increasing your site’s visibility but also foot traffic to your brick-and-mortar business.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse3">
                            <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What kind of businesses need local and national SEO?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse3" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Businesses that have a physical location or any business that serves a set geographic area should be using local SEO. Location-based businesses that can greatly benefit from local SEO includes medical services, restaurants & cafes, hospitality, local retailers, law offices, and many more.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse4">
                            <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What is the difference between SEO and local and national SEO?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse4" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>The difference between SEO and local SEO is the geographical component. Traditional SEO is the process of improving your site’s visibility on a global scale, whereas local SEO allows you to target users in your community or service area.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse5">
                            <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What is included with local and national SEO services?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse5" class="collapse">
